# Financial Risk Solvency Inadmissible Assets Loans Amount

## identifier
de5634

## type
float

## definition
Report the inadmissible value of loans as per the solvency standard.  

The inadmissible assets are: 
a) holdings in an associated or subsidiary entity which is a Financial Services entity;
b) assets with too little diversification, are too illiquid or have too great an exposure to one obligor of low credit standing; and 
c) amounts by which the recorded value of an asset exceeds its net realisable value.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=FinancialRisk.Solvency.InadmissibleAssetsLoans.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.05
- period=instant
